{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"378f4163-6b3a-44f0-a867-aa3a69b86a2f","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Change base images\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally.\n- Run `dotnet restore` to update dependencies.\n- Check NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) for `11.x` versions and update them.\n- Review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for anything affecting your app.\n- Build and test: `dotnet build && dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9f4ff1ed-63cb-4cc4-bc36-507ba457688d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":357,"requestId":"D002:190179:196E4EE:1CD769D:69E821CF"},"id":"60f75527-debf-4db9-8f63-b41b19ca031c","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:18:14.548Z","parentId":"c771c5f5-d8ad-4cea-8c3e-a0c7fa019b39"}
